---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout title="Liturgy" description="Guides to Byzantine worship — the Divine Liturgy, the daily services, symbolism, and the rhythm of feasts and fasts throughout the year.">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <div class="section-label" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Liturgy</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title" style="font-size:34px;">Understanding Byzantine Worship</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">
        The central act of Eastern Christian life is the Divine Liturgy — an ancient service where heaven and earth are believed to overlap. Everything here is designed to help you enter it, whether you're preparing for your first visit or your hundredth.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="article-surface">
    <div class="container--narrow">

      <nav class="breadcrumbs">
        <a href={`${base}/`}>Home</a>
        <span class="sep">›</span>
        <span style="color: var(--beeswax);">Liturgy</span>
      </nav>

      <!-- Intent-driven routing -->
      <h2 class="routing-heading">What brings you here?</h2>

      <div class="intent-grid">

        <a href={`${base}/liturgy/walkthrough/`} class="intent-card">
          <div class="intent-icon">☦</div>
          <div class="intent-body">
            <h3>I want to understand the Divine Liturgy</h3>
            <p>A complete step-by-step walkthrough — from the preparation of the gifts to the final blessing. What happens, what it means, and what you'll see and hear.</p>
            <span class="intent-link">Walk through the Liturgy →</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href={`${base}/liturgy/whats-happening-now/`} class="intent-card">
          <div class="intent-icon">📱</div>
          <div class="intent-body">
            <h3>I'm at a service and I'm lost</h3>
            <p>Quick-reference cards you can pull up on your phone. Each moment: what's going on, what to do, what it means. Covers the Liturgy, Vespers, and general etiquette.</p>
            <span class="intent-link">Open the quick guide →</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href={`${base}/liturgy/symbolism/`} class="intent-card">
          <div class="intent-icon">🕯</div>
          <div class="intent-body">
            <h3>I want to understand what I saw</h3>
            <p>Why incense? Why do they face east? What's behind those doors? The symbolic language of Byzantine worship — the building, the senses, the vestments, the gestures.</p>
            <span class="intent-link">Explore the symbolism →</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href={`${base}/liturgy/feasts-and-fasts/`} class="intent-card">
          <div class="intent-icon">📅</div>
          <div class="intent-body">
            <h3>I want to understand the church calendar</h3>
            <p>The Twelve Great Feasts, Pascha, the four fasting seasons, and why Eastern Christians spend nearly half the year fasting — and the other half celebrating.</p>
            <span class="intent-link">Learn the rhythm →</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href={`${base}/tools/first-visit/`} class="intent-card">
          <div class="intent-icon">🚪</div>
          <div class="intent-body">
            <h3>I'm visiting a Byzantine church for the first time</h3>
            <p>What to wear, where to stand, when to sit, whether you can receive Communion, and what to do when you have no idea what to do. Practical, no-stress guidance.</p>
            <span class="intent-link">Read the First Visit guide →</span>
          </div>
        </a>

      </div>

      <!-- The Other Services -->
      <hr class="divider" />

      <h2 class="section-heading">The Daily Cycle of Prayer</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">The Divine Liturgy does not exist in isolation. It is surrounded by a daily cycle of services inherited from the monastic tradition. In parishes, most of these are celebrated only on major feast days or during Lent. In monasteries, they are the pulse of every day.</p>

      <div class="service-grid">
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Vespers</h3>
          <p>The evening service. Begins the liturgical day — in Byzantine reckoning, the day starts at sunset, not midnight. Themes of creation, light, and thanksgiving. The hymn <em>Phos Hilaron</em> ("O Gladsome Light") is among the oldest Christian hymns still in use.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Matins</h3>
          <p>The morning service. Longer and richer than Vespers. Themes of resurrection and light breaking into darkness. The <em>Canon</em>, a complex poetic composition of nine odes, forms its centerpiece. On Sundays, the Resurrection Gospel is read.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>The Hours</h3>
          <p>Short services marking the first, third, sixth, and ninth hours (roughly 6 AM, 9 AM, noon, 3 PM). Psalms, troparia, and prayers. They punctuate the day with remembrance of Christ's Passion.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Compline</h3>
          <p>The last prayer before sleep. Themes of repentance, trust, and surrender. The Great Compline of Lent includes the penitential Canon of St. Andrew of Crete.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Hymns to know -->
      <hr class="divider" />

      <h2 class="section-heading">Four Hymns Worth Knowing</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">The Liturgy is almost entirely sung. No instruments — human voices only. These four recur so frequently that learning them is the fastest way to feel at home:</p>

      <div class="hymn-list">
        <div class="hymn-item">
          <div class="hymn-name">The Trisagion</div>
          <div class="hymn-text">"Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us."</div>
          <div class="hymn-note">Sung three times, invoking the Trinity. One of the oldest hymns in Christianity, attested from the fifth century.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hymn-item">
          <div class="hymn-name">The Cherubic Hymn</div>
          <div class="hymn-text">"Let us who mystically represent the Cherubim, and who sing the thrice-holy hymn to the life-creating Trinity, now lay aside all earthly cares…"</div>
          <div class="hymn-note">Accompanies the Great Entrance. The congregation sets aside everything to join the angelic worship.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hymn-item">
          <div class="hymn-name">"We Have Seen the True Light"</div>
          <div class="hymn-text">"We have seen the true light. We have received the heavenly Spirit. We have found the true faith, worshipping the undivided Trinity, who has saved us."</div>
          <div class="hymn-note">Sung after Communion. The entire Liturgy summarized in four lines.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hymn-item">
          <div class="hymn-name">"It Is Truly Right"</div>
          <div class="hymn-text">"It is truly right to bless you, O Theotokos, ever blessed and most pure, and the Mother of our God."</div>
          <div class="hymn-note">Sung during the anaphora. Its place at the heart of the Eucharistic prayer reflects the connection between the Incarnation and the Eucharist.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Further reading -->
      <div class="reading-box">
        <h3>Further Reading</h3>
        <p>Alexander Schmemann's <em>For the Life of the World</em> is the essential starting point: short, luminous, and transformative. His <em>Introduction to Liturgical Theology</em> goes deeper into structure and history. For a walk-through of the Liturgy itself, see Hugh Wybrew's <em>The Orthodox Liturgy</em> or the <em>Divine Liturgy: An Anthology for Worship</em> (Ukrainian Greek-Catholic Church). The catechism <em>Christ Our Pascha</em> covers sacraments and liturgical life in §§ 432–620.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Routing heading */
  .routing-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--beeswax);
    margin: 8px 0 24px;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }

  /* Section headings */
  .section-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--beeswax);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }
  .section-intro {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--censer-smoke);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .section-intro em {
    color: var(--aged-vellum);
  }

  /* Intent cards */
  .intent-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .intent-card {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 20px;
    background: var(--icon-wall);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--gold-10);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 24px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.3s, transform 0.15s;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .intent-card::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 20%;
    right: 20%;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--gold-40), transparent);
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.3s;
  }
  .intent-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--gold-15);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    opacity: 1;
  }
  .intent-card:hover::before {
    opacity: 1;
  }
  .intent-icon {
    font-size: 28px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
    opacity: 0.7;
    width: 36px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .intent-body h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 19px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--beeswax);
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .intent-body p {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--censer-smoke);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0 0 10px;
  }
  .intent-link {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--halo-gold);
    letter-spacing: 0.3px;
  }

  /* Service grid */
  .service-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  .service-card {
    background: var(--icon-wall);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--gold-10);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 24px;
  }
  .service-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--beeswax);
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  .service-card p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--censer-smoke);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .service-card em {
    color: var(--aged-vellum);
  }

  /* Hymn list */
  .hymn-list {
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  .hymn-item {
    padding: 20px 0;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--gold-06);
  }
  .hymn-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  .hymn-name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--beeswax);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .hymn-text {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 15px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #D4C5AB;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .hymn-note {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--censer-smoke);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Reading box */
  .reading-box {
    margin: 48px 0 80px;
    padding: 24px;
    background: var(--gold-04);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .reading-box h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--beeswax);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }
  .reading-box p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--aged-vellum);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .reading-box em {
    color: var(--censer-smoke);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .service-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .intent-card { padding: 20px; }
    .intent-icon { font-size: 24px; width: 28px; }
  }
</style>
